<HEADLINE> IOC Formally Expels Six Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUSANNE, SWITZERLAND, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The International
Olympic Committee (IOC) formally expelled six members at its 108th
session held here today.
</P>
<P>
The six who have been expelled are Agustin C. Arroyo of
Ecuador, Zein El Abdin A. Gadir of Sudan, Jean-Claude Ganga of
Congo, Lamine Keita of Mali, Sergio Santander Fantini of Chile,
and Paul Wallwork of Samoa.
</P>
<P>
The expulsion of the first five were recommended on January 24
by the IOC ad hoc commission to investigate the conduct of certain
IOC members involved in the bidding process of the winter Olympic
games in the Salt Lake City.
</P>
<P>
Wallwork was added to the recommendation when the ad hoc
commission presented its second report to the IOC executive board
on March 11. 
</P>
</TEXT>
