<HEADLINE> Ruling Coalition Established in Estonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Three parties victorious in the
last parliamentary elections agreed on Wednesday to form ruling
coalition, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The leaders of the Isamaaliit, Moodukad and Reformierakond
which jointly won 53 of the 101 seats in the March 7 elections,
signed an agreement to this effect in Tallinn, capital of the
Baltic republic.
</P>
<P>
The leader of Isamaaliit and candidate for the post of premier,
Mart Laar, said the new cabinet would mostly pursue the old
foreign policy priorities such as the speedy integration into
Western institutions and the development of good-neighborly
relations with Russia
</P>
<P>
"Relations with our neighbor to the east will improve more
rapidly the faster we integrate into West European organizations,"
Laar said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
