<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Outgoing EU Executive Body Issues Statement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The outgoing European Commission
issued on Wednesday a statement on its current status. Following
is the statement in full text:
</P>
<P>
"We have resigned, and have no desire or intention of remaining
in office a moment longer than we have to.
</P>
<P>
The Treaty, however, requires us to remain in office until a
new commission is in place. We accordingly urge the member states
to appoint, according to the procedures of the Treaty, a new
commission without delay.
</P>
<P>
Under the Treaty, the powers of the commission in the current
circumstances are not limited.
</P>
<P>
We have, nonetheless, decided to exercise our powers in a
restrictive manner, i.e. to deal with current and urgent business,
and to comply with our institutional and legal obligations, but
not to take fresh political initiatives." 
</P>
</TEXT>
