sides have reaffirmed their commitment to the Agreed Framework of
1994, in its entirety," he said.
</P>
<P>
"He hopes that the two countries will continue to successfully
address other issues of importance, thus contributing to the
reduction of tension in the Korean Peninsula and in the region,"
Eckhard added.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK and the United States announced on Tuesday that they
had reached an agreement under which Pyongyang will allow U.S.
access to the Kumchang-ri underground site suspected by the U.S.
as a nuclear facility, while the U.S. will take step to improve
its ties with the DPRK.
</P>
<P>
Under the 1994 Agreed Framework, an international consortium
will provide the DPRK with two light water reactors while the DPRK
will freeze its graphite reactors.
</P>
<P>
A senior U.S. official said he believed that the latest accord
would help improve the atmosphere for KEDO implementation.
