<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
have concluded his two-day working visit in Rwanda and returned
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
During his visit in Rwanda, Museveni and his Rwandan
counterpart Pasteur Bizimungu had held talks in Kigali on regional
security and other issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
A press release from the President's Office said Wednesday
evening that the two leaders issued a communique at the end of
Museveni's visit to the country which started on Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The two heads of state had reviewed the progress made so far in
the region, especially the situation in the Democratic Republic of
Congo (DRC).
</P>
<P>
They reiterated their already publicly stated legitimate
involvement in
non-involvement of the rebel Congolese Rally for Democracy in the
negotiations for a ceasefire.
</P>
<P>
