<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat
has said the Palestinian people has the right to declare an
independent state on May 4 when the interim period of Palestinian
self-rule stipulated in the Oslo Accords expires.
</P>
<P>
Arafat made the remarks Wednesday evening in Gaza in meeting
Liu Zhihai, Chinese representative to Palestine.
</P>
<P>
To move the peace process forward and continue peace talks with
Israel are the strategic options of the Palestinian people and the
Palestinian National Authority will continue to do so, Arafat said.
</P>
<P>
But he said that the Mideast peace talks have entered a
stalemate again while all signed agreements between the
Palestinians and Israel have not been implemented properly.
</P>
<P>
But the Palestinian side is not responsible for that, Arafat
stressed.
</P>
<P>
China is an important country in maintaining the world peace
and in supporting justice, and the Palestinian people will never
forget the great support the Chinese government and people
rendered to them.
</P>
<P>
China is not a country seeking self-interest in the Mideast and
the Palestinian people believe that China will continue to play a
great role in moving the Mideast peace process forward, Arafat
said.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Liu said that China will cherish its friendly
relationship with the Palestinian people and will continue to make
contributions to the peace in the region. 
