<HEADLINE> ARATS President Plans Taiwan Visit For This Autumn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIPEI, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Association for Relations
Across the Taiwan Straits (ARATS) and the Straits Exchange
Foundation (SEF) have agreed in principle on ARATS President Wang
Daohan's visit to Taiwan this autumn.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached today in Taipei by ARATS Deputy
Secretary General Li Yafei and SEF Deputy Secretary General Jan
Jyh-horng, who agreed that Wang and his wife will have a five or
six day visit.
</P>
<P>
After their meeting, Li told a press conference that they
discussed implementation of the four-point consensus reached by
Wang Daohan and SEF Chairman Koo Chen-fu last autumn in Shanghai.
He said that he is here to prepare for Wang's visit and to lay a
foundation for discussions of details of the visit.
</P>
<P>
Li explained that Wang's visit is a continuation of the high-
level ARATS and SEF dialogue on political and economic issues.
</P>
<P>
He said that they have heard SEF's suggestions on Wang's visit
and will report them to the ARATS chairman and that ARATS will
study them carefully and discuss them with SEF on the next visit.
</P>
<P>
ARATS also confirmed its invitation of Jan to the mainland and
said it is willing to invite SEF Vice-Chairman Shi Hwei-yow to the
mainland in June. During these visits, he said, they can make
arrangement for further exchanges of views on Wang's Taiwan visit.
</P>
<P>
Jan said that this is the first time for the two to sit down
face-to-face to discuss Wang's Taiwan visit and that this is
itself successful because they can understand each other's point
of view, which is helpful for further discussions.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting between Li and Jan, SEF Vice-Chairman Shi
Hwei-yow had a protocol meeting with Li Yafei.  
</P>
