<HEADLINE> Sino-Swiss Foundation For Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- SSPF, a Swiss-Chinese foundation,
has helped establish a joint-venture in China, according to China
Trade News.
</P>
<P>
The 27 million U.S. dollar foundation, set up in 1997, was
designed to promote bilateral economic cooperation, with 80
percent of its investment coming from Switzerland and 20 percent
from China.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss government has encouraged small and medium-sized
companies to invest abroad, the newspaper quoted a Swiss official
as saying. Sino-Swiss trade in 1997 was worth 1.486 billion US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Swiss investment in China has grown a great deal in the 1990s.
More than 400 Swiss companies are already in China, including the
giant ABB, Roche, Ciba-Geigy, and Nestle.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990318.0061 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Financial Sector Progressing in Addressing Y2K Problem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese financial
official said here Thursday that China's financial sector has been
progressing greatly in addressing the Y2K problem and is confident
to ensure a smooth and successful transition into the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
Chen Jing, director general of the Payment System and
Technology Department of the People's Bank of China (PBC), made
the point to the Global 2000 Coordinating Group meeting.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, he pointed out, the efforts and progress have not
been made known to international financial sectors and other
relevant areas due to lack of information dissemination about
them.
</P>
<P>
Chen said, "We have the highest level commitment and focus from
both the Chinese government and the financial sector to solve the
Y2K problem."
</P>
<P>
The State Council of China issued directives last August
identifying it as the key industry to solve the Y2K problem, and
the PBC, the central bank, called a meeting of the presidents from
all the banks to map out a framework for solving the Y2K problem
in the financial sector, making clear that the president of each
bank is personally responsible for solving the Y2K problem.
</P>
<P>
A Finance Industry Year 2000 IT Project Office has been set up
to provide leadership for the financial sector in this regard and
all the commercial banks and policy banks have set up their own
offices alike, he said.
</P>
<P>
The PBC has also issued Year 2000 Testing Guidelines, laying
out both the recommended schedule and standards for the Y2K
compliance testing, he added.
</P>
<P>
On the current status in practical work, Chen said the PBC and
the commercial banks as well as policy banks have completed
hardware upgrading and nearly all system and application software
has been modified and put in place.
</P>
<P>
Chen said the whole sector is in a stage for further system
upgrading, internal and interbank testing and contingency plan
formulating.
</P>
<P>
According to established plans, he said, all financial
institutions must complete all the internal test of application
systems as well as interbank testing of critical systems by May
and finalize formulation and testing of contingency plans at the
same time.
</P>
<P>
External and online testing will be completed by September,
Chen said.
</P>
<P>
Taking the case at PBC, Chen said modification of the 22
centrally developed application systems have been close to
completion, acceptance criteria and contingency plan are being
finalized and over 90 percent of its local branches have finished
preliminary testing plans.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the Y2K readiness of the major business systems at
PBC, Chen said all the critical systems, including the Electronic
Interbank System, the Local Clearing House Systems, the Central
Bank Accounting System, the Foreign Exchange Transaction System
and RMB Interbank Loan System , the Bond Settlement System ,
Information Management System for Treasury, Currency Issue,
Statistics and Foreign Exchange will totally become Y2K compliant
by May.
</P>
<P>
Mentioning China's five commercial banks which handle a wide
range of business and have a lot of complex applications, Chen
said they are now focusing on system testing, acceptance and
contingency planning and their external and online testing will
also be finished by September.
</P>
<P>
Chen expressed confidence that with the cooperation and support
of the electrical power and telecommunications ministries the
financial sector can fulfill its mission to solve the Y2K problem,
minimize Y2K risks and ensure a smooth and successful transition
into the 21th century.
</P>
<P>
Global 2000 Coordinating Group is an informal grouping of
banks, securities firms and insurance companies whose aim is to
identify and resource areas where coordinated initiatives will
facilitate efforts by the global financial community to improve
the readiness of global markets to meet the challenges created by
the year 2000 date change. It is holding a three-day meeting in
Singapore from Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
