<HEADLINE> Ukraine Rules Out Alleged NATO Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A senior Ukrainian official Thursday
rejected the allegation that Ukraine will soon become a member of
the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), describing it as a
"provocation."
</P>
<P>
The rumor had been concocted to mislead Ukraine's balance-
oriented diplomatic policy, Vladimir Gorbulin, secretary of the
Ukrainian Committee on Security and Defense, said at a symposium
here on NATO.
</P>
<P>
He quoted President Leonid Danilovich Kuchma as saying that at
present it is too early for Ukraine to join NATO.
</P>
<P>
However, Gorbulin noted that Ukraine, under the United Nations
Charter, has the right to become a member of any military or
political organization though it has not yet presented an official
application for NATO membership so far.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he called on NATO to take into consideration the
interests and concerns of all European countries in its expansion
process, saying that Ukraine supports the establishment of a new
European security system. 
</P>
