<HEADLINE> Estonian Parliament Elects New Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Estonia's new parliament on
Thursday elected Toomas Savi, of the ruling center-right coalition,
as its speaker, Interfax reported.
</P>
<P>
Savi, 53, was elected by a vote of 55-46. He was nominated for
the post by the Fatherland Union, the party of Moderates and the
Reform party, which together won 53 of the 101 seats in the March
7 parliamentary elections.
</P>
<P>
A native of Tartu, Estonia, Savi graduated from the Tartu
University as a specialist in sports medicine and had served as
head doctor of the Soviet athletic team, mayor of Tartu and
speaker of the former parliament. 
