<HEADLINE> Cambodian PM Calls for Enhancing Public Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Prime Minister Hun
Sen Thursday called for strengthening the battle on kidnapping and
other crimes against social security.
</P>
<P>
At a ceremony to appoint new governors, Hun Sen ordered related
authorities to take united action at any cost to ensure social
security in the shortest time possible.
</P>
<P>
He said he is very concerned about deterioration of society's
general security, especially security of foreign investors. Many
of them have been chased out of the country, he added.
</P>
<P>
"Although I am the prime minister of the country, I'm still not
dare to let my children go far. So we should take severe measures
to crack down on the armed robberies and kidnappings. Let the
criminals have no place to hide," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Most of the kidnapping victims in the past years have been
prominent business figures or family members, particularly ethnic
Chinese. Western aid workers and high-ranking government officials
have not been immune.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Hun Sen ordered banning illegal gambling in
Phnom Penh which was believed often related to abductions and
other crimes. 
</P>
