<HEADLINE> Mugabe Stresses Importance of Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe
Thursday said the African countries should pay attention to
education.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe said this at the opening ceremony of the two-day African
 education ministers conference in Harare, capital of Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
The conference's objectives are to examine developments in
education in Africa and to chart future courses of action.
</P>
<P>
The president stressed a revised agenda on education in Africa
should guide African countries in achieving education for all.
</P>
<P>
He said that major challenges facing African education systems
include access to education, relevance and effectiveness of
education, complimentary learning modalities, and capacity
building.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the United Nations Children's Fund
(UNICEF), almost a billion people will enter the 21st Century
unable to read or write, almost two-thirds of whom will be women.
</P>
<P>
Of the people who will be illiterate, more than 130 million are
of school-going age and are in the developing world, he said.
</P>
<P>
According to a draft program of action of decade of education,
Africa now faces a literacy rate of as low as 40 percent and over
200 million illiterate adults.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe said: "Poverty, ignorance, hunger and disease have
remained our major problems which must be vigorously tackled by
all of us."
</P>
<P>
"Through education, we can spur our peoples to become full
citizens and social actors in the global village," he said. "We
should thus strive to overcome problems associated with falling
enrolment ratios, low completion and high drop-out rates as well
as irrelevant curricula so that our peoples can be prepared to
enjoy full social and economic lives.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out, "We fully realize that learning for life in the
21st Century will require that children or learners be equipped
not only with a basic education in literacy and numeracy but also
with more advanced and complex skills for living that serve as the
foundation for life." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
