<HEADLINE> Tamil Rebels Attack Military Camp in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 18 (Xinhua) -- the Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam (LTTE) rebels Thursday attacked a military camp at Mannar in
northwestern coast of Sri Lanka with mortars and heavy artillery
causing considerable damage to the installation, military sources
here said Thursday evening.
</P>
<P>
The sources said at least six soldiers and two civilian
employees at the camp were killed while 14 others were seriously
injured in the incident.
</P>
<P>
An ammunition dump in the camp was also blown up by the rebels
in the course of the attack. the extent of casualties suffered by
the rebels of the LTTE is unknown at present, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a war against the government since
1983 for a separate state in the north and east of the country in
the course of which over 55,000 persons have been killed. 
</P>
