<HEADLINE> Microsoft's Chinese Version Of New Web Browser </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The world's largest software
provider, Microsoft, released the Chinese version of its Internet
Explorer 5.0 today.
</P>
<P>
Microsoft is scheduled to release versions in 9 languages today
but because of time difference, the IE 5.0 is being made available
in China earlier than in the US.
</P>
<P>
The IE 5.0 will make interaction with the Internet quicker and
more convenient and it is easier for professionals to develop,
deploy and manage, according to Julia Wu, general manager of
Microsoft (China) Co., Ltd.
</P>
<P>
However, the IE 5.0 seems less powerful to some than its
predecessor the IE 4.0, which was released in Sep. 1998. But, Wu
says, the new browser may not be a revolution, but it will be a
popular product. The IE 5.0 is 20-25 percent faster than the IE 4.
0 and 75 percent faster than its rival the Navigator 4.5.
</P>
<P>
The new browser allows a computer to be used for real-time
radio or television reception from the Internet. It contains the
Windows Media Players and can be applied to VCDs, which might make
it popular in China, the world's largest VCD market.
</P>
<P>
The new IE also allows users to choose from the nine search
options like Yahoo and Excite. And, it can be downloaded from the
Internet or purchased through traditional channels and is smaller
than the 4.0 version. The IE 5.0 has 6.5 megabytes, but the 4.0
has 12 megabytes so downloading time is shorter.
</P>
<P>
In addition to Microsoft's Chinese language Website, Internet
users can download IE 5.0 from 13 Chinese Internet service
providers and Internet content providers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
