<HEADLINE> Ukrainian Shot Putter Banned for Two Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian shot putter Vita Pavlysh
has received a two-year ban from her national athletics federation
after failing a dope test during the athletics indoor world
championships earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
Pavlysh, who won the world indoor title with a toss of 21.43
meters, denied any wrongdoing, saying that the banned medical
substances may have resulted from treatment she was undergoing for
knee and elbow injuries. 
