<HEADLINE> Southwestern China City's Folk Art Festival in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Nanning, capital of southwestern
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, will host an
international folk art festival in November.
</P>
<P>
Mayor Lin Guoqiang told a press conference today that the
Nanning International Folk Song Art Festival will have three
themes -- culture, trade, and tourism.
</P>
<P>
The festival was formerly called the Guangxi International Folk
Song Festival and was an annual event that started in 1993.
</P>
