<HEADLINE> China Continues Renovating Rural Electric Networks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- China will continue the
renovation work on its rural electric networks in 1999 as part of
the government efforts to improve basic infrastructure and the
domestic market.
</P>
<P>
This is based on a decision made during a State Planning
Commission and National Electrical Power Corporation meeting that
opened Thursday in the capital of Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
Those present called for increased activity in all projects and
decided that no new projects will be started in 1999. To ensure
quality, they urged regional governments to improve project audits
and to crack down on corrupt construction practices.
</P>
<P>
The renovation work was a major Chinese Government decision in
1998. The Government also decided to lower the price of
electricity in rural areas to allow people there to pay the same
rates as in urban areas.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the Government allocated 42.5 billion yuan in spending
on projects in 1,500 counties nationwide. 
</P>
