<HEADLINE> Chinese College Students Mark Art Gala </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- China's three million college
students have held a series of activities to mark this year's
first art gala scheduled to last through June.
</P>
<P>
The '99 National Art Gala for College Students will exhibit the
active spirit of college students and will commemorate both the 80
th anniversary of May Fourth Movement and the 50th anniversary of
the founding of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Education Chen Zhili said this gala will present
the great achievements China has scored over the past four decades.
Chen called on education departments at all levels to combine
college art education with quality education.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the organizing committee note that gala will be
divided into two parts -- the first part between February and June
10, and the second on the latter part of June.
</P>
<P>
