<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Lower on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SINGAPORE, March 18 (Xinhua)-- Share prices ended slightly lower
on Singapore Stock Market Thursday with the benchmark Straits
Times Index down 4.09 points to end at 1,466.07.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover declined to 127.45 million units valued at
222.13 million Singapore dollars (about 128.88 million U.S.
dollars). Losers led gainers by 107 to 100 with 220 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
UIC w99 was the most heavily traded stock with a volume of 14.12
million shares. TC ongIntHK came second with 9.97 million units
transacted. Eagle US$ was the next with 8.96 million shares
traded.
</P>
<P>
SIA led the gainers of the day up 30 cents to close at 7.60
Singapore dollars. It was followed by C&AMP;C and SIA 200 that gained
15 cents to finish at 7.25 Singapore dollars and 7.60 Singapore
dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 and OCBC F led the losers of the
day shedding 30 cents to finish at 21.10 and 11.90 Singapore
dollars respectively. DBS F, JurShip and UOB F fell 20 cents to
end at 13.10, 6.65 and 10.20 Singapore dollars respectively.
CityDev and RothmansI sank 15 cents to close at 7.90 Singapore
dollars and 9.70 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Traders attributed the lower stock prices to the weak local
market sentiment.
</P>
<P>
Institutional investors were generally sidelined amid the
corporate earnings season which so far had seen mostly weak
earnings and the foreign tranches of local banks were among the
top losers. 
</P>
