<HEADLINE> Shandong to Authorize Private Domestic Travel Agencies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, March 18 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province
plans to allow individuals to apply for domestic travel service
licenses, according to a provincial tourism official.
</P>
<P>
Shandong will remove restrictions on private applications for
travel service licenses and permit individuals to operate domestic
travel agencies, according to Li Deming, director of the Shandong
Provincial Tourism Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Private travel agency classification will include agencies
established by individuals or partnerships and limited-liability
travel agencies jointly established by groups of from two to 50
individuals, as well as limited-liability agencies established by
an individuals in collaboration with state-owned or collectively
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Individuals involved in the establishment of the latter
classification of agencies must hold at least a 51 percent stake
in the venture, according to Li.
</P>
<P>
He added that government regulations must be followed when
establishing private travel agencies and related ventures must
have qualified management professionals.
</P>
<P>
Shandong has more than 250 travel agencies, including 45
international ventures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
