<HEADLINE> Zhejiang's Retail Sales Recovering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province
reported 35.7 billion yuan in retail sales in the first two months
of this year, up 6.7 percent over the same period last year,
according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
After adjusting price indices, the actual growth rate is 9.3
percent, the Zhejiang Provincial Statistics Bureau said.
</P>
<P>
Consumption recovery was more apparent in the rural areas than
in the urban areas, the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
The most significant increases in sales were reported in the
catering industry, tourism, mobile phones, and household
appliances, figures show.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang is among the most economically developed areas in China.
</P>
