<HEADLINE> China Reinsurance Company Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The China Reinsurance Company (
China Re), which grew out of the Reinsurance Company under the
People's Insurance Company of China (PICC), was established here
today.
</P>
<P>
The PICC was disbanded in October 1998, and its subsidiaries,
including life insurance, property insurance and reinsurance, have
all become independent insurers.
</P>
<P>
The newly created China Re has a registered capital of 3
billion yuan, including 100 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Ma Yongwei, chairman of the China Insurance Regulatory
Commission, attended today's founding ceremony, and said that the
establishment of China Re will help further perfect the country's
insurance market and prompt the sector to develop on a sound and
smooth track.
</P>
<P>
China Re's predecessor, PICC, had its reserve fund increased
from 4.87 billion yuan in 1996 to a current six billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
PICC, now China Re, the country's only state-owned insurer
specializing in reinsurance, has developed into a modern
reinsurance company based on international standards, according to
general manager Dai Fengju. 
</P>
</TEXT>
