<HEADLINE> King Sihanouk Approves Name List of Senators </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian King Norodom
Sihanouk signed the name list of senators Thursday, completing the
process of creating a senate in the country.
</P>
<P>
Sihanouk signed the name list presented by three major parties
that have seats in the National Assembly.
</P>
<P>
The Senate comprises 61 members, of whom 31 are from the
Cambodian People's Party (CPP), 21 from FUNCINPEC, seven from the
Sam Rainsy Party and two appointed by the king.
</P>
<P>
Chea Sim, president of CPP, was appointed president of the
Senate, while the first and second vice presidents came from the
FUNCINPEC party.
</P>
<P>
The formation of the Senate is part of a political deal between
the CPP and FUNCINPEC that led to the establishment of the
coalition government last November.
</P>
<P>
The National Assembly approved the constitutional amendments
after three days of debate from March 4, paving the way for the
creation of the Senate.
</P>
<P>
The Senate will be sworn in on March 25 and hold its first
session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
