<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Set to Host Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The city of Ningbo in east
China's Zhejiang Province, one of the country's economic
powerhouses, will host an investment and trade fair on June 8-11.
</P>
<P>
The fair will list 160 key projects in 15 sectors for overseas
investment, including projects in the electronics, chemical and
pharmaceutical sectors.
</P>
<P>
The event will also feature tourism promotions and a seminar
covering cooperation between non-public enterprises and
multinational companies.
</P>
<P>
Some 3,000 overseas investors are expected to attend the fair,
according to the Zhejiang Provincial Foreign Investment Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The use of overseas funds and trade during 1998 enabled
Zhejiang to recover from a downturn lasting several years.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang's export and import for the first two months of this
year hit 2.15 billion US dollars, up 10.2 percent on the 1998
period. The province approved 149 overseas-funded enterprises,
with total contracted overseas capital surging 28 percent to 235
million US dollars. 
</P>
