<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Plunge in Tokyo Following Previous Gains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices nosedived in Tokyo
Thursday following huge gains in the previous three trading days,
with the key Nikkei index closing below 16,000 for the first time
in three days.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange, which surged almost 780
points over the past three days, plunged 550.19 points, or 3.38
percent, from Wednesday's close to end at the day's low, 15,717.92,
after climbing to as high as 16,303.12.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, lost 28.85 points or 2.29 percent to 1,231.
24.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section ballooned to the highest level so
far this year at 1,301.38 million shares, up from 1,223.49 million
shares Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Sakura Bank was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Investors took a break following the recent sharp gains, said a
dealer.
</P>
<P>
Share prices fell in all business sectors, except for the
brokerage industry, the insurance industry and the service sector,
traders said.
</P>
<P>
The key market gauge is expected to remain weak Friday, as
investors are not likely to take clear positions ahead of a long
weekend, they said. Monday is a holiday in Japan.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers outpaced
gainers 973 to 289, with 64 issues ending unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
