<HEADLINE> Hubei to Build Cemetery For Flood Martyrs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hubei Province
plans to build a cemetery commemorating the nineteen people who
lost their lives while fighting last summer's floods.
</P>
<P>
These martyrs were officers and soldiers of the People's
Liberation Army who made great contributions to the rescue effort
in Jiayu County, which was destroyed by the severe flooding of
August 1, 1998.
</P>
<P>
At the time, 57,000 local residents were forced to flee their
homes and thousands of homes were destroyed.
</P>
<P>
The cemetery will cover an area of 3.6 hectares, and the
buildings on it will include a monument, a memorial hall, and a
statue and the graves of the martyrs. 
</P>
