<HEADLINE> International News Corp. Opens Office in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Media tycoon Rupert Murdoch's
News Corporation (News Corp.) opened a representative office in
Beijing today, the first major international media company to do
so.
</P>
<P>
"The opening of our new representative office in Beijing marks
another milestone in News Corporation's business development in
China," said Gareth Chang, executive director of News Corp. and
executive chairman of Star TV, at the opening ceremony held today.
</P>
<P>
News Corp. investments in China include its Star TV Network and
the Star TV joint venture, Phoenix Satellite TV, which currently
broadcasts the Phoenix Chinese Channel reaching over 45 million
households, according to Chang.
</P>
<P>
"In addition, News Corp. has joint ventures in Beijing with the
People's Daily (PDN Xinren Information Technology Co. Ltd.) and in
Tianjin (Golden Mainland Production Co. Ltd.). Its other interests
include ChinaByte, a major website in China, and Golden Mainland,
a leader in post-production services with a client base including
CCTV and major provincial stations.
</P>
<P>
Last year, News Corp.'s 20th Century Fox Studio enjoyed strong
success in China with the release of the films "Titanic" and "Home
Alone."
</P>
<P>
"Developments in the media industry in China, including rapid
technological change, make us optimistic about the potential for
our business here," said Chang.
</P>
<P>
News Corp. is one of the world's largest media companies with
total assets of 36 billion U.S. dollars and total annual revenues
of 14 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Its commercial empire covers the United States, Canada, the UK,
Australia, Latin America and Asia, with operations in television,
newspapers, magazines and books, the production and distribution
of movies, and other areas. 
</P>
