<HEADLINE> China to Open First On-line Export Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The 85th China Export Commodities
Fair will open on April 15 in Guangzhou, and, simultaneously, on
the Internet.
</P>
<P>
For the first time, the fair will break out beyond the 160,000-
square-meter-site near the Guangzhou Railway Station, and connect
to businesses all over the world via the 'net.
</P>
<P>
Like previous fairs, the first on-line Guangzhou fair will
present exhibitions and services and trading booths.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises taking part in the on-site fair will be able to
post commercial information on the Internet fair by themselves at
any time, as a search engine has been created classifying
enterprises and commodities.
</P>
<P>
The on-line fair also provides discuss rooms with various
topics where viewers will be able to discuss things freely. There
will also be rooms for negotiations, coded for secrecy.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, E-mail and fax services will be readily available.
</P>
<P>
The Internet was used for the first time three years ago during
the 80th fair when a website was opened, and the 83rd fair
employed the Internet to send invitations to over 2,000
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The test version of this first on-line Guangzhou fair is
already on-line at: http://www.cecf-gz.com, or: http://cecf.com.
cn.  
</P>
