<HEADLINE> Guangdong Reports Sustained Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province reported sustained and steady economic growth for the
first two months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The province's industrial value-added hit 33.72 billion yuan,
up 12.3 percent on the previous year's period.
</P>
<P>
The accumulated retail sales volume jumped 12 percent after
deducting price hikes to end the period at 61.75 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The outstanding loan volume for Guangdong banks grew 17.37
billion yuan on the figure for the end of February 1998.
</P>
<P>
The province invested 17.52 billion yuan in basic construction
and real estate development, a year-on-year rise of 34.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's foreign trade status remained grim, with export
volume falling 24.6 percent to 8.305 billion US dollars. However,
the import volume inched up by 0.2 percent to 7.22 billion US
dollars.  
</P>
