<HEADLINE> Construction of Grain Depots Makes Headway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Construction of 370 new
depots for the central government grain reserves is in full swing
since the work began later last year.
</P>
<P>
Information from a recent national meeting on the subject in
Shijiazhuang, provincial capital of Hebei, said these depots under
construction account for 95 percent of the total new grain depots
the central government intends to build this year.
</P>
<P>
The State Development Planning Commission and State Grain
Reserve Administration decided to build 388 new grain depots
across the country in response to the call made last June by the
State Council, China's highest governing body.
</P>
<P>
The entire construction will cost 18.2 billion yuan, and when
completed, the 388 new grain depots will be able to store 27.6
billion kilograms of grain.
</P>
<P>
All 388 new grain depots are expected to be completed and in
use before this year's autumn harvest.
</P>
<P>
Since construction began, state departments concerned have set
up a leading group for the task, and established a joint working
office under the leading group. Various localities around the
country have also set up similar organs to ensure a smooth
construction procedure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
