<HEADLINE> Hainan sees Rising Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Official statistics show that
Hainan, China's southernmost island province and the country's
largest special economic zone, continued to attract increased
overseas investment in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Actual foreign investment for the year hit 717 million US
dollars, up 1.6 percent on the previous year's period, according
to the Hainan Commerce and Trade Commission.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, the United States, Taiwan, Singapore and Japan
accounted for 88 percent of total investments.
</P>
<P>
Investment in infrastructure facilities, agriculture, industry
and tourism continued to rise during the year, according to the
commission.
</P>
<P>
Hainan has approved over 8,000 overseas-funded enterprises,
with actual foreign investment exceeding eight billion US dollars.
</P>
