used by scientists on Earth by means of the latest technology
developed by the National Defense Science and Technology
University of China.
</P>
<P>
This technology, known as the remote science communication and
data management imitation system, links communications between
space and Earth through the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Researchers will be able to access equipment in a space station
such as robots and video cameras in real time via the Internet
through this system.
</P>
<P>
Experts believe this will serve as an essential technological
guarantee for unmanned experiments in the spacecraft of the future.
</P>
<P>
The system was successfully developed by the university in
central China after three years of effort.  
