<HEADLINE> ARATS President to Visit Taiwan This Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIPEI, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Wang Daohan, president of the
Association for Relations Across the Taiwan Straits (ARATS), will
visit Taiwan this fall, ARATS announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Wang is expected to travel with his wife to Taipei and the
southern port city of Kaohsiung during his five or six days in
Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Word of the trip came after Li Yafei, ARATS' deputy secretary
general, exchanged views this morning with Jan Jyh-horng, deputy
secretary general of the Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF), on
matters relating to Wang's Taiwan visit and ARATS-SEF dialogue.
</P>
<P>
Li said the four-point consensus reached between Wang Daohan
and SEF Chairman Koo Chen-fu last October is an important basis
for the contact and exchanges between ARATS and SEF at present,
noting that consensus will be crucial to improve cross-Straits
relations.
</P>
<P>
ARATS believes that Wang's Taiwan visit is a continuation and
development of the high-level talks between ARATS and SEF which
began last year.
</P>
<P>
Wang will exchange views with Koo on the political and
economic issues and other aspects of cross-Straits relations. Wang
will also meet with a number of officials.
</P>
<P>
ARATS hopes that Wang's visit will bring about further
achievements following Koo Chen-fu's mainland tour last year, and
said this depends on concerted efforts from both sides.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
