<HEADLINE> Iverson Leads 76ers to Victory over Indiana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Allen Iverson contributed 39
points to lead the Philadelphia 76ers to a 114-110 home victory
over the Indiana Pacers on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Iverson, currently the league's top scorer with 28.1 points per
game, overcame his dismal performance on Monday which saw him only
chip in 17 points in 76ers' 73-74 loss to Orlando, to score 10 in
the fourth quarter as Philadelphia overcame an eight-point deficit.
</P>
<P>
Reggie Miller scored 27 points for Indiana, which leads the
Central Division with a 15-7 record.
</P>
<P>
In Atlanta, Tim Hardaway scored 24 points as the Miami Heat
held off the Atlanta Hawks for their sixth straight victory, 86-85.
</P>
<P>
Mourning and P.J. Brown each scored 14 points for Miami (18-5),
which has the best record in the Eastern Conference.
</P>
<P>
In Orlando, the Magic produced a 14-1 run in the final minutes
to seal a 103-94 victory over the Chicago Bulls.
</P>
<P>
Darrell Armstrong scored a season-high 23 points off the bench
for the Magic (17-7), who trail Miami by 1-1/2 games in the
Atlantic Division.
</P>
<P>
At Golden State, Malik Rose scored seven of his 17 points in
the fourth quarter and fellow-reserve Steve Kerr added a season-
high 14 as the San Antonio Spurs posted their ninth straight
victory, 82-78 over the Golden State Warriors.
</P>
<P>
At Detroit, rookie Vince Carter scored 17 of his 28 points in
the fourth quarter as the Toronto Raptors posted their third
victory in as many nights, 103-101 over the Detroit Pistons.
</P>
<P>
In Charlotte, Eddie Jones scored 29 points and Elden Campbell
pulled down a career-best 19 rebounds to help the Hornets win over
the Phoenix Suns 119-111.
</P>
<P>
At New Jersey, Stephon Marbury made a successful home debut
with 29 points to help the Nets snap an eight-game losing streak
with an 88-87 win over the Dallas Mavericks.
</P>
<P>
In Denver, Hakeem Olajuwon scored 26 points and Othella
Harrington added 23 off the bench as the Houston Rockets beat the
Denver Nuggets 114-109.
</P>
<P>
In Boston, Kenny Anderson contributed 21 points to lead the
Celtics to a 118-84 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
