<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading South African newspapers Thursday:
</P>
<P>
The Citizen:
</P>
<P>
-- The Arms and Ammunition Amendment Bill, which restricts the
owners of licensed firearms to lending their weapons only to other
licensed firearm owners, was approved by the National Assembly
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Star:
</P>
<P>
-- As a reconciliation gesture, Winnie Madikizela-Mandela has
given the wedding ring that Nelson Mandela slipped on her finger
at their wedding in 1958 to the 13-year-old daughter of Paul
Erasmus, the former security policeman whose job was to discredit
her.
</P>
<P>
Sowetan:
</P>
<P>
-- Former clergyman and anti-apartheid activist Allan Boesak
was convicted in the Cape High Court Wednesday on four charges of
fraud and theft involving about 1.377 million rand (222,000 U.S.
dollars) in foreign donor welfare funds. 
