<HEADLINE> South Korean Soccer Chief's DPRK Visit Postponed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, March 18 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's top soccer official
has to postpone a scheduled visit to the Democratic People's
Republic Korea (D.P.R.K.), it was reported here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Chung Mong-joon, president of South Korean Football Association,
had planned to begin a six-day visit to D.P.R. Korea on Friday to
discuss sports exchanges and the possibility of holding some of
the 2002 World Cup games in Pyongyang.
</P>
<P>
But soccer officials of the two sides had failed to reach an
agreement on the details of the visit, according to South Korean
association officials.
</P>
<P>
Chung had initially planned such a visit in mid-January but
called off the trip later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
