<HEADLINE> Exports Soaring in Southeast China's Fuzhou City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Fuzhou city in Southeast China's
Fujian Province saw 29.2 percent in export growth during the first
two months this year.
</P>
<P>
The year-on-year increase is a result of local efforts in
exploring new markets and optimizing the export product mix.
</P>
<P>
The city now has 103 trade partners, 13 of which were developed
in 1998, and has been exploring new business in Africa, the Middle
East, Eastern Europe and North America.
</P>
<P>
It also gives priority to the development of 23 large domestic
exporters, including overseas-funded and foreign trade companies
each with over 10 million US dollars worth of exports a year and
state-run manufacturers, each with over five million US dollars a
year in exports.
</P>
<P>
Exports of hi-tech products like electronics and information
items are on a stable rise and grew by 50 percent in 1998 from the
previous year. 
</P>
