<HEADLINE> Shanghai Establishes High-tech Industry Framework </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai has basically
established a high-tech industry framework since the introduction
of intensive restructuring in the late 1980s.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that each of 19 major products
developed by the city's high-tech sector held a 20 percent or more
share of respective national markets by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
The list of products included automobiles, specialty steel
products, power generation equipment, elevators, integrated
circuits and program-controled switchboards, as well as optical
fiber, color TV tubes, air conditioner compressors and gene
engineered products.
</P>
<P>
For example, Satana cars hold a 48 percent share of the
national market, with total 1998 sales for 235,200 units standing
at 25.2 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's respective market shares for thin steel plates and
high-quality rolled steel exceed 28 percent. 
