<HEADLINE> Internet Advertising to Become New Favorite in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Internet advertising sector
will be much favored in China amidst a booming computer market and
the Internet surfing craze, according to China Commercial News.
</P>
<P>
With no time and space limitations, Internet advertising has
better opportunities for development compared with other
advertising methods. Internet surfers only need to click the mouse
to get information, and through e-mail, customers and the staff of
enterprises can keep in direct contact with each other.
</P>
<P>
"But Internet advertising is only at a nascent development
stage in China, and it has not produced its due economic returns,"
an Internet advertisement designer has said.
</P>
<P>
According to him, several factors stand in the way of
development. The most obvious ones are the low-level of design
ability and inappropriate distribution.
</P>
<P>
Major players in the sector are now stepping up their efforts
to upgrade technology in this regard and substantial achievements
have already been made.
</P>
<P>
China's Internet surfers are expected to hit 4.5 million by
2000, and experts believe Internet advertising will become a
favorite sector in the near future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
