<HEADLINE> Chinese Muslims Making Journey To Mecca </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Xinjiang Airlines has carried 1,
101 Muslim pilgrims to Mecca in Saudi Arabia this year.
</P>
<P>
China's Xinjiang Autonomous Region has the largest Muslim
population in China and several thousand usually make the annual
pilgrimage at this time of year.
</P>
<P>
According to Hu Yamin, assistant general manager of Xinjiang
Airlines, which is based in Xinjiang's capital of Urumqi, his
company has had 4 charter flights to Mecca this year.
</P>
<P>
The airlines began the service in 1995, and in the last 5 years,
nearly 10,000 pilgrims have made the holy journey on 40 specially-
chartered flights.
</P>
<P>
This year's pilgrims are scheduled to return to Urumqi with the
chartered flights of the airlines in mid April, Hu says.  
</P>
