<HEADLINE> CDB to Issue 10 billion Financial Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The China Development Bank (CDB)
is to issue 10 billion yuan of floating rate bonds, after
receiving approval from the People's Bank of China (PBOC).
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that CDB has issued bonds of this kind.
The issuing interest rate has been set at 4.945 percent, with the
fixed interest rate discrepancy standing at 1.165 percent.
</P>
<P>
The interest rate of the bonds is set each year by adding the
fixed interest rate discrepancy to the one-year fixed deposit
interest rate determined by the PBOC, which is currently 3.78
percent.
</P>
<P>
The bonds can be traded in the interbank market after their
issuance.  
</P>
</TEXT>
