<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Finland to Strengthen Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- China is willing to strengthen
and advance ties with Finland and raise bilateral cooperation in
various fields to a new level, Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Tang, who arrived in Helsinki Tuesday at the invitation of his
Finnish counterpart Tarja Halonen, made the remarks during
separate meetings with Finnish President Martti Ahtisaari and
Prime Minister Paavo Lipponen.
</P>
<P>
Tang said Sino-Finnish relations had witnessed rapid growth in
recent years through the efforts of the two countries' leaders.
</P>
<P>
Though geographically distant from each other, Finland and
China have no historical contentions nor contradictions in
interests. The peoples of the two countries have fostered sound
friendship with the continuous deepening of mutual understanding,
the Chinese foreign minister said.
</P>
<P>
He observed that both countries should review their long-term
interests and lay a solid foundation for their mutually beneficial
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The next year marks the 50th anniversary of the establishment
of diplomatic ties between Finland and China, Tang said. The
Chinese government and people are willing to join hands with the
Finnish government and people to bring the Sino-Finnish ties
closer together.
</P>
<P>
Echoing Tang's viewpoints on bilateral ties, President
Ahtisaari said Finland is very glad to establish close relations
with China and is satisfied with the rapid development of Sino-
Finnish ties.
</P>
<P>
He said Finland values and attaches importance to its
cooperation in judiciary practices and human rights and the
achievements gained through dialogue.
</P>
<P>
He hoped the two countries will expand their cooperation on the
basis of equality, mutual benefit and mutual respect.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Lipponen expressed his satisfaction with the
earnest and rapid implementation of the various agreements which
he struck with his Chinese counterpart during his visit to China
last year.
</P>
<P>
He was particularly satisfied with the two countries'
cooperation in the field of forestry and expressed a willingness
to further strengthen this mutually beneficial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of Sino-European relations, the Chinese foreign
minister said China and Europe should strengthen cooperation and
explore new dialogues that not only conform to the fundamental
interests of both, but would also promote Asia-Europe cooperation,
world peace, stability and development.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that Finland would play an active role in promoting
the development of China-Europe ties and the elimination of the
European Union's discriminative measures against China's trade
when it holds the rotating presidency of the EU in the second half
of the year.
</P>
<P>
Ahtisaari said Finland supports the efforts by the EU and China
to build an active and broad partnership. He acknowledged that
both countries will enjoy favorable conditions to deepen
cooperative measures once Finland assumes the EU presidency.
</P>
<P>
Finland is the first leg of Tang's five-European-nation tour.
The Chinese foreign minister is scheduled to head for Stockholm to
continue his visit after winding up the trip to Finland Thursday
afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
