percent from 260 million dollars in 1997 to 117 million dollars in
1998. Argentina, Brazil and Paraguay were listed as the principal
trade partners of Uruguay in 1998, taking 55 percent of the
country's total exports and providing 43 percent of imports.
Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay are the four members of
the customs union Mercosur, which is also the largest trade bloc
in Latin America. (Uruguay-Trade Deficit) 
