<HEADLINE> Ecuador's Former Interim President Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador's former interim president
Alarcon Rivera has been arrested on charges of abuse of power, the
Supreme Court announced on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He was arrested Tuesday after the court ordered an arrest
warrant.
</P>
<P>
The prosecutor was Cecilia Calderon, a deputy in the leftist
party.
</P>
<P>
In July, 1997, Calderon accused Rivera of illegally employing
over 1,000 people in 1996 when he was president of the National
Chamber of Representatives. He said the positions were redundant
and unnecessary because the employees were doing nothing for the
parliament.
</P>
<P>
After an investigation that lasted one year, the Supreme Court
found him guilty of many other crimes and ordered a preventative
arrest warrant against him.
</P>
<P>
Rivera pleaded innocent and said facts would prove his
innocence.
</P>
<P>
He was elected parliament speaker in June 1996 and became
interim president in February 1997. He finished his term on
August 19, 1998. 
</P>
