<HEADLINE> Myanmar Records 125 Fire Cases in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A total of 125 fires broke out in
Myanmar in January, 10 cases more than the same period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
The official evening newspaper The City News said Wednesday
that the fires killed nine people and 413 cattle and injured six
people, destroyed 407 houses, five factories and one godown and
left 1,617 people homeless.
</P>
<P>
Of the fire cases, 86.4 percent were caused due to negligence,
the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar registered the highest number of fire cases in December
of 1998 with 116, which destroyed 426 houses and left 1,673 people
homeless.
</P>
<P>
With rainfall getting less throughout the country and the
possibility of outbreaks of fires increasing, the authorities are
reminding officials of fire brigades in states and divisions to
step up fire prevention in cooperation with the local authorities.
 
