institutions while 1.1 million to other suppliers, he added.
</P>
<P>
The country's total foreign debt stands at near four billion
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Honduras was due to pay more than 304 million dollars this year,
including 109 million dollars in obligations related to bilateral
debt. The Club of Paris, however, agreed to a delayed payment of
its debt for 1999, 2000 and 2001, after Hurricane Mitch devastated
the country. 
