<HEADLINE> Colombian President Ends Visit to Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Colombian President Andres
Pastrana ended a two-day visit to Spain on Wednesday with a
Spanish promise to support the peace process in his country.
</P>
<P>
In his talks with Spanish King Juan Carlos I, Prime Minister
Maria Aznar and Foreign Minister Matutes Juan, the Spanish side
voiced support for the peace process in Colombia and promised to
provide places for negotiations between the Colombian government
and guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Pastrana hoped that by mediating between the government and
guerrillas, Spain could become a member of "a group of friendly
nations of Colombia".
</P>
<P>
The two sides also agreed to further strengthen bilateral
economic and trade cooperation and several agreements were signed
for the purpose.
</P>
<P>
To attract more foreign capital, the Colombian president
promised to amend the country's constitution so as to give a more
favorable legal framework for foreign investment. Pastrana also
promised to improve other domestic environment for foreign
investment. 
