<HEADLINE> Rio Group Foreign Ministers Meet to Prepare Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Foreign ministers from the 14
Rio Group member countries will meet in the Mexican port city of
Veracruz on Thursday to prepare for a summit meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican Foreign Ministry said in a press release on
Wednesday that the foreign ministers will analyze the agenda for
the summit and try to adopt a common position before the June 28-
29 meeting with the European Union.
</P>
<P>
The Rio Group is made up of the Latin American countries of
Argentina, Bolivia, Brazil, Colombia, Chile, Ecuador, Mexico,
Panama, Paraguay, Peru, Uruguay, Venezuela and a representative
from the Caribbean Community.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry sources said the ministers are expected to
discuss the international financial crisis and possible measures
to reduce its impact on the economies of the region.
</P>
<P>
They will also analyze cooperative measures in order to
strengthen the Rio Group in international forums, and to improve
efficiency. 
