<HEADLINE> Bartoli Warms up for World Cup Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Michele Bartoli warmed up
for the defence of his World Cup crown by winning the Tirreno-
Adriatico cycling race on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Italian took the overall lead by finishing second in
Sunday's fifth of eight stages.
</P>
<P>
Jan Svorada of the Czech Republic made a sprint finish to win
Wednesday's final leg, 164 kilometers along the Adriatic coast
from Civitanova Marche to San Benedetto del Tronto.
</P>
<P>
Svorada completed the stage in four hours, 22 minutes, 14
seconds while Bartoli, the world's top-ranked rider, clocked 36:01:
30 for the total 1,412 kilometers over eight days. 
