<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ningbo Development Zone Enjoys Surging Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The export volume for the Ningbo
Development Zone in east China's Zhejiang Province surged 53.6
percent to 66.57 million US dollars in the first two monthsyear-on-
year.
</P>
<P>
The growth resulted from local efforts to increase exports to
Europe and countries in South Africa and the Americas, as well as
the zone's success in maintaining the stable volume of exports to
the Australian and Asian markets.
</P>
<P>
Exports to Europe and the Americas surpassed the volume to Asia
for the first time in history during the two-month period.
</P>
<P>
Substantial growth was recorded for exports of high-tech and
high value-added items, including machinery, communications
facilities, industrial products and farm equipment.
</P>
<P>
Local foreign trade companies expanded cooperation with banks
and insurance companies in order to ensure the safety of
settlements in foreign currencies.
</P>
<P>
Nine major trade companies in the zone exported products valued
at 35.67 million US dollars during the two-month period, up 107
percent. The export volume for 440-odd foreign-funded enterprises
in the zone jumped 18.4 percent to 30.9 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The zone is exerting great efforts to ensure a 10 percent
increase exports this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
