<HEADLINE> Beijing to Host Computer Exposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The third International Computer
Distribution Exposition China '99 is scheduled to be held in
Beijing between May 23 and 26, according to the Ministry of
Information Industry (MII).
</P>
<P>
Liu Chunlu, vice-director of the Computer and Micro-electronics
Research and Development Center of MII, was quoted by today's
China Daily as saying that the exposition will fuel the
development of the country's IT (information technology) industry
as well as the economic information systems.
</P>
<P>
More than ten countries and regions, including the United
States, Japan, Australia, Republic of Korea, Singapore, Hong Kong
and Taiwan, are scheduled to send more than 180 business
delegations to the event.
</P>
<P>
On the exhibition list are many famous companies including
Epson, Motorola, Autodesk, Sharp, Cisco, Symantec, Samsung,
Beijing Telecom and Legend.
</P>
<P>
They are expected to present their advanced technologies
featuring enterprise systems, PC series, multimedia,
telecommunications, network products, software, data connection,
ISP (internet service provider) access service and ICP (internet
content provider) Chinese information scanning.
</P>
<P>
A number of international technology shows and lectures will
also be given during the event, according to the organizing
committee.
</P>
<P>
Jointly sponsored by the MII, the Ministry of Science and
Technology, China Council for the International Trade, and the
US's Ziff-Davis and IDG companies, the event is expected to
attract more than 80,000 domestic and overseas visitors.
</P>
