<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poor Population Down in Shaanxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The number of poor people in
northwest China's Shaanxi Province has been cut to one million
from the five million in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Fourteen additional counties in the province have been taken
off the list of State-level poverty-stricken counties since last
year, encompassing a population of 700,000.
</P>
<P>
The per capita grain availability for these people reached more
than 350 kilograms last year, and their per capita cash income,
more than 700 yuan (84.3 U.S. dollars), officials said.
</P>
<P>
The province has so far delivered more than 570 million yuan (
68.7 million U.S. dollars) in loans to poor people to help them
find new ways to earn a living, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Local government has also helped farmers to master advanced
agricultural technology, they added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
