<HEADLINE> Inner Mongolia Introduces Extensive Ecological Program (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Engbey area of the Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region's Hobq Desert has wild hares playing on
grassland under rows of trees and wild ducks and gray cranes on a
man-made lake.
</P>
<P>
A regional Forestry Department official says that it is just
one part of a large ecological protection screen running from the
Da Hinggan Ling Mountains in to the Alxa Gobi Desert. But it's
hard to imagine that just a few years ago the land was nothing but
a desert.
</P>
<P>
Since the 1990s, sandstorms have hit Alxa League to the west of
the region every year, affecting not only the region, but even
Beijing and surrounding areas.
</P>
<P>
Now China is placing emphasis on the ecological development of
Inner Mongolia, according to a State Forestry Administration
official. Of 10 major forest projects of China's central
government, five are in the region.
</P>
<P>
About a third of the "Sanbei (northern, northeastern, and
northwestern China) Forest Protection Screen" is in the region. (
more)
