<HEADLINE> Cardoso to Visit Germany and Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian President Henrique
Cardoso will make an official visit to Germany on April 15 and 16
to strengthen relations between the two countries, the Foreign
Ministry announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Ministry said that President Cardoso will meet with
Chancellor Gerhard Schroder as well as German bankers and
businessmen.
</P>
<P>
As Germany is the current president of the European Union,
President Cardoso will also talk with German representatives on
issues concerning the summit meeting of Latin America, the
Caribbean countries and the European Union, which will be held on
June 28 and 29 in Rio de Janeiro.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, trade between Germany and Brazil reached 7.5 billion U.
S. dollars, while German investment in Brazil was worth more than
10 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Following his visit to Germany, Cardoso will make an official
visit to Portugal on April 17.  
