Lukashenko on Wednesday denied rumors that Russian nuclear arms
will return to his country in response to NATO enlargement.
</P>
<P>
"There was no talk of the return of nuclear arms during
conversations with Russian President Boris Yeltsin," Interfax
quoted Lukashenko as saying at a meeting with labor
representatives in Dokshitsy, a city in Belarus' northeast Vitebsk
