<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dynamo Kiev Eliminate Real Madrid at Champions League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Dynamo Kiev of Ukraine made a
stunning shot on Wednesday by ousting defending champions Real
Madrid from the European soccer Champions' League.
</P>
<P>
Dynamo, who topped their section of the Champions' League in
December after patches of sometimes brilliant play, hit the
heights again despite months without competitive soccer to defeat
Real 2-0 for a 3-1 aggregate victory.
</P>
<P>
Kiev now have a real chance of becoming the first team from
Ukraine to be crowned European champions in the final in Barcelona
on May 26.
</P>
<P>
While Kiev qualified for the semifinals of the Champions League
for the first time since 1987, Juventus took their by now
customary place in the last four after a late goal saved them from
elimination in Greece.
</P>
<P>
Juventus, beaten finalists last year and bidding for their
fourth successive European Cup final, were trailing 1-0 to
Olympiakos Piraeus and heading out of the competition on the away
goals rule with the aggregate scores level at 2-2.
</P>
<P>
But with five minutes to play skipper Antonio Conte struck the
goal that kept Juventus's dreams of glory alive.
</P>
<P>
Back in Italy, Inter Milan's hopes of winning the European Cup
for the first time since their back-to-back wins of 1964 and 1965
were ended by Manchester United, seeking their first European Cup
success since their only victory in 1968.
</P>
<P>
United, 2-0 up from the first leg at Old Trafford, defended
resolutely for the first hour, but finally cracked in the 63rd
minute when Nicola Ventola took advantage of some sloppy United
covering to lash home from close range.
</P>
<P>
That goal inspired Inter to increase the tempo and seek a
second, but they failed to find another goal.
</P>
<P>
Instead, substitute Paul Scholes, who had only been on for 11
minutes, put the issue beyond doubt when he also scored from close
range to force the draw and give United a 3-1 aggregate victory.
</P>
<P>
The result keeps United on course for a treble of domestic
league and cup and European Cup and also meant that they had
eliminated an Italian side for the first time in their 42-year
European competition history.
</P>
<P>
Bayern Munich are also chasing a domestic double and success in
Europe and stayed on course for their first European Cup victory
since 1976 after crushing Bundesliga rivals Kaiserslautern 4-0
away for a 6-0 aggregate win.
</P>
<P>
The draw for the semifinals will be made in Geneva on Saturday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
