<HEADLINE> Dow Moves Lower Day After Breaking 10,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Down Jones industrial
average moved down Wednesday a day after briefly breaking the
10,000 milestone.
</P>
<P>
At the close of trading, the Dow fell 51.06 at 9,879.41, nearly
121 points away from 10,000. The index crossed the five digit
milestone briefly, then turned back and closed with a loss of
28.30 points Tuesday
</P>
<P>
The Dow's decline came as a result of higher interests in the
bond market. The 30-year Treasury bond was down 5/16 point at
midday, pushing its yield to just under 5.5 percent from 5.47
percent Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also lower. The Standard &AMP; Poor's
500 index fell 8.54 to 1,297.82 and the technology heavy Nasdaq
index fell 10.30 at 2,428.97.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index was down 3.43 at 610.65 and the American Stock
Exchange index was down 0.48 at 715.83. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies was down 0.74 at 398.43.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 6-to-5 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,368 up, 1,628 down and 567
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 749.79 million shares from 738.80
millions in the previous session. 
</P>
