<HEADLINE> Gloom Hits Main European Stock Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Main European stock markets closed
lower after the Dow continued its decline from Tuesday, when it
touched the 10,000-point mark only for a while.
</P>
<P>
London's blue chips FTSE 100 carried on from where it left off
in the last session, failing to make any headway. The index fell
almost 1 percent, shedding 61 points to close at 6,140.6.
</P>
<P>
"It's been a thin day volume wise, and we'd have needed the Dow
above 10,000 to force a FTSE recovery," said one trader from a
European bank.
</P>
<P>
Even strong hints from the Bank of England that it is
considering further interest rate cuts failed to stir investors.
</P>
<P>
The central bank's thinking was revealed in minutes from its
Monetary Policy Committee, released Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, the leading shares fell back again after a brief
rally that took the market into positive territory. The benchmark
Xetra Dax index ended 0.56 percent lower at 5,062.59, a drop of
just over 28 points.
</P>
<P>
In Paris, shares also reversed out of the red and then slipped
back as the Dow faltered. The Cac 40 index finished 16.34 points
lower at 4,170.01. 
</P>
