<HEADLINE> UK Unemployment Starts To Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The rapid slowdown in the UK
economy has finally hit the job market with unemployment rising
for the first time in six months.
</P>
<P>
The official figures released by the Office for National
Statistics (ONS) Wednesday, showed jobless numbers rising 4,300 to
1,311,000 in February.
</P>
<P>
Economists said the data would soothe inflation fears and pile
further pressure on the Bank of England to cut lending rates again
to revive the economy.
</P>
<P>
However, when looking at the other side of the coin, the total
number of people in jobs has also risen, to 27.3 million.
</P>
<P>
The apparent contradiction in the figures is explained by the
fact that the total workforce is expanding allowing rises in both
employed and unemployed.
</P>
<P>
ONS figures for earnings growth show wages rising 4.3 percent
in the three months to January over the same period a year
earlier.
</P>
<P>
Both the job and wage figures raise hopes of another cut in
interest rates in April, showing that the UK's economic slowdown
has begun to bite hard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
