<HEADLINE> IOC President Vows to Prevent Scandal Crisis From </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUSANNE, Switzerland, March 17 (Xinhua) -- International
Olympic Committee (IOC) President Juan Antonio Samaranch pledged
here Wednesday that it would be his highest priority to make sure
that the crisis caused by the Salt Lake City scandal would never
happen again during the remaining time as the IOC head.
</P>
<P>
"During the last weeks we have worked very hard to find a way
that it will never happen again," said Samaranch. "Through the
remaining time of my presidency of the IOC I intend it to be our
highest priority."
</P>
<P>
"Our main role in the wake of this very important session is to
take the necessary steps to be certain that his very sad episode
in the history of the international Olympic movement never happens
again," said Samaranch a few moments before the IOC 108th session
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 78-year-old IOC chief also confirmed his intention to stay
in his position until 2001, when he is due to retire. 
</P>
