<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraq annnounced on Wednesday that clerics from a
foreign country were involved in the asssassination of Iraq's
most senior Shiite cleric Mohammed Mohammed Sadiq al-Sader.
</P>
<P>
In a communique read on Iraq's national television, Iraqi
General Security Directorate said Iraqi security authorities
had arrested four assassins including Iraqis and clerics from a
foreign country, adding another assassin is still at large.
</P>
<P>
But he did not name the foreign country.
(BC-Iraq-Assassination Results) 
</P>
